cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.GR, cs.MS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with triangulations and Voronoi diagrams, which are fundamental concepts in computational geometry. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents an iterative algorithm for transforming a given triangulation into a well-centered one. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the paper mentions numerical algorithms that prefer well-centered primal-dual mesh pairs. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is possible as the paper presents visual results of applying the algorithm to two-dimensional meshes. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is also possible as the paper presents a new characterization of well-centeredness and an optimization-based heuristic for achieving it.
